diagnosis: The primary issue preventing profitability is the absence of trades executed over the test period, indicating overly restrictive or misconfigured trade filters.
rootCauses: Overly restrictive execution filters leading to no trades being taken.
Misconfiguration in the trading strategy, possibly in the alignment checks or session filters.
Potential logical errors in the code preventing the detection of valid setups.
Incorrect or too stringent environment configuration values.

suggestions.description: Relax execution filters to allow more trades to be taken.
codeChanges: src/config/executionFilterConfig.ts: Ensure 'requireHtfAlignment', 'requireBosInDirection', and other checks are correctly implemented and not overly restrictive.
suggestions.reasoning: Relaxing the execution filters will allow more potential trades to be evaluated, increasing the likelihood of executing trades.

suggestions.description: Adjust the minimum FVG size and OB wick ratio to be less restrictive.
suggestions.reasoning: Lowering the threshold for FVG size and OB wick-to-body ratio will allow more setups to qualify under current market conditions.

suggestions.description: Increase the stop loss buffer to allow more room for price movements.
suggestions.reasoning: A larger stop loss buffer can prevent premature trade exits due to normal market volatility, although it may also decrease the R:R ratio.

suggestions.description: Enable debug logging for the first 1000 trade evaluations to gather more insight into filter decisions.
codeChanges: src/strategy/v2/SMCStrategyV2.ts: Temporarily adjust logging conditions or add more detailed logging around filter checks.
suggestions.reasoning: Enabling detailed debug logging will help identify why no trades are being executed by providing visibility into the decision-making process.

expectedImpact: These changes are expected to increase the number of trades taken by relaxing overly restrictive filters, thereby providing a better opportunity to assess the strategy's true performance and make further optimizations based on actual trade data.
